            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Third week of February – Kaamulan Festival. Celebrated from the third week of February until the second week of March, the famed yearly Kaamulan Festival records a growth of visitors at- tending this colorful and authentic cultural activity. Both foreign and local tourists are in total awe of the ethnic music, rituals and dances of the seven different tribes of Bukid- non. Meaning “gathering for a purpose” in the tribal language, Kaamulan is celebrated by the whole province as thanksgiving to the Magbabaya (God) for bountiful harvest and continuing prog- ress. Kaamulan is highlighted by a street dancing revelry.</li>
                <li>2. May 15 – City Fiesta in honor of Patron San Isidro every May 15.</li>
                <li>3. June 15 – Aldaw ta Malaybalay, the City’s Foundation Day.</li>
            </ol>

