            <h3>Malaybalay City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Enjoy a healthy lifestyle by brisk walking and jogging at the Capitol Grounds on early mornings or late afternoon. The Provincial Capitol Grounds is perfect for sports and other activities for families and groups to bond and enjoy the refresh- ing site and cool air.</li>
                <li>2. Play frisbee and soccer games during lazy afternoons and carefree weekends at the Capitol Grounds.</li>
                <li>3. Commune with nature through rugged walking and running at the Kaamulan Tree Park. The Kaamulan Tree Park is a vast area of pine trees, creek, and natural garden that is located downside of the Provincial Capitol.</li>
                <li>4. Experience a spiritual sanctuary of art and nature and partake a Breakfast with the Monks at the Monastery of Trans- figuration every second Sunday of the month. The Monastery of the Transfiguration, a religious site of the Benedictine Monks, is a famous destination for tourists, a favorite venue for weddings and home to the world renowned Monks Blend Coffee produced by the Monastery Farms.</li>
                <li>5. Enjoy a variety of delectable delicacies and scrumptious recipes at Anton’s, Cuadra, Rey’s Grill, Benedict’s, Centro Chicken Neck, Bukidnon Brew Café, Mint Leaf Café and Le’ Café.</li>
            </ol>
